Phase 2: E2E on AKS with 3 isolation levels and Kata VM sandboxing

Security hardening:
- All images built from Azure Linux 3 (no Debian) via rustup
- AKS API + ACR + AOAI + KV locked to caller IP + AKS egress
- AOAI disableLocalAuth (Entra-only), custom seccomp DaemonSet
- restricted PodSecurity on all sandbox namespaces

Three isolation levels (standard/enhanced/confidential):
- standard: runc + RuntimeDefault seccomp on clawpool
- enhanced: runc + Localhost seccomp azureclaw-strict on clawpool
- confidential: Kata VM isolation on katapool

azureclaw up --isolation parameter, pre-built image import,
auto federated credentials per sandbox namespace

E2E verified: GPT-4.1 through sandbox, WI auth, Content Safety,
Prompt Shields. All 3 levels deployed and tested on AKS.

Key fixes: WI client_credentials grant, seccomp sendmmsg/recvmmsg,
entrypoint skip router in AKS mode, kata-vm-isolation RuntimeClass
